article.headline: San Francisco 87, Morgan St. 74
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- Angelo Caloiaro scored 19 points with a game-high eight rebounds and San Francisco broke its three-game losing streak with an 87-74 victory over Morgan State on Tuesday night. Perris Blackwell also added 19 points for the Dons (10-6), who shot 53.8 percent from the field for their best performance against a Division I foe this season. Ameer Ali recovered from a scoreless performance in his previous game to lead Morgan State (2-9) with a career-high 21 points, but he couldn't prevent the Bears from falling to 1-6 on the road this season.
